The op-ed by Dr. Jill Biden and Senator Bill Frist discusses their visit to the Dagahaley refugee camp in Dadaab, Kenya, where Somali refugees have sought refuge from the severe famine in their country. They describe the desperate conditions and heartbreaking choices faced by the people, including a mother who had to leave one of her children behind in order to save the other. They highlight the efforts of the international community in providing aid to the region, but emphasize that more assistance is needed to prevent further deaths. They urge individuals to contribute towards the relief efforts and emphasize the importance of addressing the underlying issue of food insecurity to prevent future crises. The authors conclude by emphasizing that everyone has the power to make a difference and help those in need.